content:
library(shiny)
library(bslib)
library(ggplot2)

rw_impov_grp <- read.csv("exported_fig_3_data.csv")



# Define UI for app that draws a histogram ----
ui <- page_sidebar(
 
   titlePanel("Citations to different research genres during the Covid-19 Pandemic"),
  
  # Create a new Row in the UI for selectInputs
  sidebar = sidebar(
  
   selectInput("citing_date",
               "Pandemic Month:",
               c("All", unique(as.character(rw_impov_grp$citing_date)))
               ),
   
   selectInput("citingcorona",
               "Citing item has corona:",
               c("All", unique(as.character(rw_impov_grp$citingcorona)))
               ),
   
   
   selectInput("citedcorona",
               "Cited item has corona:",
               c("All",unique(as.character(rw_impov_grp$citedcorona)))
               ),

    br(),
    sliderInput("plotwindow",
                "plotrange in months:",
                min = min(rw_impov_grp$citing_date),
                max = max(rw_impov_grp$citing_date),
                value = c(0,median(rw_impov_grp$citing_date)),
                step = 1
                )
  
  
  ),
  
  navset_card_underline(
    title = "Visualizations",
    
    # Panel with table ----
    nav_panel("Table", DT::dataTableOutput("table")),
    
    # Panel with plot ----
    nav_panel("Plot (citing x cited)", plotOutput("plot"))
    
  )
)



server <- function(input, output) {
  
  # Filter data based on selections
  output$table <- DT::renderDataTable(DT::datatable({
    data <- rw_impov_grp
    if (input$citing_date != "All") {
      data <- data[data$citing_date == input$citing_date,]
    }
    if (input$citedcorona != "All") {
      data <- data[data$citedcorona == input$citedcorona,]
    }
    if (input$citingcorona != "All") {
      data <- data[data$citingcorona == input$citingcorona,]
    }
    data
  }))

  
  output$plot <- renderPlot(
    ggplot(rw_impov_grp[rw_impov_grp$citedcorona == input$citedcorona & rw_impov_grp$citingcorona == input$citingcorona,],
    aes(x=citing_date, y=percent, label=cited_type_agg)) +
    geom_line(aes(linetype = cited_type_agg, color = input$citedcorona), size = 1) +
    geom_line(aes(x=citing_date, y=unique_rate), size = 0.6, color = "gray") +
    geom_col(aes(x=citing_date, y=monthlytruerefrate), position="dodge" ,size=1, fill="gray", color=NA, alpha=.05) + 
    geom_label(aes(label = label, color = input$citedcorona), label.size = 0, alpha = 0.8) +
    scale_y_continuous(breaks=seq(0, 1, by = 0.2), minor_breaks =seq(0, 1, by = 0.1)) +
    scale_x_continuous(breaks=seq(input$plotwindow[1], input$plotwindow[2], by = 3), minor_breaks =seq(input$plotwindow[1], input$plotwindow[2], by = 1),limits=c(input$plotwindow[1], input$plotwindow[2])) +
    xlab("Pandemic month (from January 2020)") +
    ylab("Proportion") +
    labs(caption="Source: OpenAlex | PubMed (document types)") +
    theme_minimal() + 
    guides(label = "none", linetype = "none", color=guide_legend(title="Corona relatedness of References")) +
    theme(legend.position = "bottom")
  )  
}

shinyApp(ui = ui, server = server)
